	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 28th 12:55 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rogues can cap their pick lock skill at 200, once they hit level 39.&nbsp;&nbsp;The skill won't go up again until after level 50, and quite a few high level zones have locked doors that require more than 200 pick lock skill to open.  However, if you use some mechanical lockpicks, your skill gets that vital boost to 204, which is enough to pick locks in Karnor's Castle, Sebilis, Charasis, and even the door in the Freeport bank.  These mechanical lockpicks are a great item for rogues to get, if they plan to do some skull-duggery in these high level zones before they get into their 50s... pre-50 rogue survivability in these zones is another matter.  ;)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
